SIMPLE: insecure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insecure
<hw>In`se*cure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
secure; not confident of safety or permanence; distrustful; suspicious;
apprehensive of danger or loss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With sorrow and <qex>insecure</qex> apprehensions.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not effectually guarded, protected, or sustained;
unsafe; unstable; exposed to danger or loss.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hurg.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The trade with Egypt was exceedingly <qex>insecure</qex> and
precarious.</q> <rj><qau>Mickle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insecurely</ent>⟦br⟧
